frost flat
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an extensive area of flat ground, subject to severe frost because of its situation.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1900 at least. Specific areas of frost flat are the Rangitaiki, Pureora, and Whirinaki areas of the Central North Island, and parts of Tasman District.
